  <prompt>
The R7 W11 POC implemented `EnrichBulletWithEntityRefs` to populate per-bullet `primaryEntityType`/`primaryEntityId`/`primaryEntityName` for click-through. With T131 expanding to 6 entity types (events / documents / matters / projects / todos), verify the enrichment logic correctly resolves entity refs for ALL 6 types — not just events. Fix any gaps.
  </prompt>

  <role>
You are a BFF service developer verifying cross-cutting projection logic across new entity types. Targeted code modification if gaps found; investigation otherwise.
  </role>

  <goal>
Every bullet rendered in Daily Briefing widget has a working entity link (primaryEntityType / primaryEntityId / primaryEntityName populated) regardless of which of the 6 channels it came from. UAT-verifiable: operator clicks ANY bullet → navigates to correct entity record.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    - Current `EnrichBulletWithEntityRefs` implementation in `DailyBriefingNarrator` (R7 W11)
    - Entity types to verify: sprk_event (existing), sprk_document, sprk_matter, sprk_project, sprk_todo (new from T131)
    - BriefingItem projection contains entity metadata per T131
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    - Per CLAUDE.md §10 + §11: modification only if gaps; no new abstractions
    - Per ADR-038: integration-heavy test pyramid for any new test additions
    - Each entity type must have a matching enrichment branch (or a generic dispatcher that handles all 5)
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      - projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/wave12-mvp-completion-plan.md (§2.1)
      - projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/CLAUDE.md
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <relevant-files>
      - src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Narrators/DailyBriefingNarrator.cs (EnrichBulletWithEntityRefs)
      - src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Narrators/DailyBriefingCollector.cs (BriefingItem source)
      - tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Narrators/DailyBriefingNarratorTests.cs
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <steps>
1. **Read current EnrichBulletWithEntityRefs** (15 min)
2. **Identify how it matches narrative text to input items** (15-30 min):
   - Today: matches by RegardingName or Title (per session prior context)
   - Verify this works for sprk_document.name, sprk_matter.sprk_matternumber/name, sprk_project.name, sprk_todo.subject
3. **Identify gaps per entity type** (30 min):
   - Per entity type: what's the human-readable name field? What's the navigation URL pattern?
   - Document each gap or confirm coverage
4. **Implement fixes for gaps** (0-2 hours depending on gap count):
   - Smallest-change additions to enrichment dispatch
5. **Add unit tests covering each entity type's enrichment** (30-45 min):
   - Mock narrative output containing entity name; verify enrichment resolves the right entity ref
6. **Build + test verification** (15 min)

  </steps>

  <tools>
    - Read / Grep / Glob
    - Edit (selective)
    - Bash (dotnet test, dotnet build)
    - TodoWrite
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    - EnrichBulletWithEntityRefs gap fixes (if any)
    - Unit test additions
    - Verification notes
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    - [ ] Enrichment branches for all 6 entity types (sprk_event already; sprk_document / sprk_matter / sprk_project / sprk_todo new or verified)
    - [ ] Unit tests cover entity-link resolution per entity type
    - [ ] `dotnet test` 0 new failures
    - [ ] `dotnet build` 0 errors
    - [ ] No new abstractions / DI / packages
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
